{{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = Ministry of Cultures |type = Ministry |logo_width = |logo_caption = |seal = |seal_width = |seal_caption = |formed = 2009 ||preceding1 = |dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction = [[Bolivia]] |headquarters = [[La Paz]] |employees = |budget = |minister1_name = [[Marko Machicao]] |minister1_pfo = Minister of Cultures |chief1_name = |chief1_position = |chief2_name = |chief2_position = |child1_agency = Vice-Ministry of Decolonization |child2_agency = Vice-Ministry of Interculturalism |child3_agency = Vice-Ministry of Tourism |website = [http://www.minculturas.gob.bo/ Ministerio de Culturas] |footnotes = }}
The '''Ministry of Cultures''' is a [[Government of Bolivia|Bolivian government]] [[Ministry (government department)|ministry]] which formulates and implements policies in the fields of culture and tourism.
The Ministry was formed through Chapter XX of Supreme Decree 29894, issued by President [[Evo Morales]] on 7 February 2009.<ref>[http://bolivia.infoleyes.com/shownorm.php?id=576 Supreme Decree 29894], 7 February 2009.</ref>
