The '''Physics Aptitude Test''' ('''PAT''') is a 2-hour subject-specific admissions [[Test (assessment)|test]] for applicants to the [[University of Oxford]] for undergraduate degree courses in [[Engineering]], [[Materials Science]] and [[Physics]] undergraduate degree courses.

The PAT is held pre-interview stage at the beginning of November. Test results are not published automatically, but candidates may request their test score as part of the usual University of Oxford feedback process.<ref>{{cite web | title =About PAT | publisher =University of Cambridge
| url =http://www.admissionstestingservice.org/our-services/subject-specific/pat/about-pat/ | accessdate = January 15, 2014}}
</ref>

